{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Trees are wonderful arenas for discovery"},{"time":4000,"text":"because of their tall stature, their complex structure,"},{"time":8000,"text":"the biodiversity they foster and their quiet beauty."},{"time":12000,"text":"I used to climb trees for fun all the time"},{"time":14000,"text":"and now, as a grown-up, I have made my profession understanding trees"},{"time":19000,"text":"and forests, through the medium of science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"The most mysterious part of forests is the upper tree canopy."},{"time":25000,"text":"And Dr. Terry Erwin, in 1983,"},{"time":27000,"text":"called the canopy, \"the last biotic frontier.\""},{"time":31000,"text":"I'd like to take you all on a journey up to the forest canopy,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and share with you what canopy researchers are asking"},{"time":37000,"text":"and also how they're communicating with other people outside of science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Let's start our journey on the forest floor"},{"time":44000,"text":"of one of my study sites in Costa Rica."},{"time":46000,"text":"Because of the overhanging leaves and branches,"},{"time":49000,"text":"you'll notice that the understory is very dark,"},{"time":52000,"text":"it's very still."},{"time":54000,"text":"And what I'd like to do is take you up to the canopy,"},{"time":56000,"text":"not by putting all of you into ropes and harnesses,"},{"time":59000,"text":"but rather showing you a very short clip"},{"time":61000,"text":"from a National Geographic film called \"Heroes of the High Frontier.\""},{"time":65000,"text":"This was filmed in Monteverde, Costa Rica"},{"time":67000,"text":"and I think it gives us the best impression of what it's like"},{"time":70000,"text":"to climb a giant strangler fig."},{"time":73000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":103000,"text":"(Growling)"},{"time":106000,"text":"(Rustling)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"So what you'll see up there is that it's really like the atmosphere of an open field,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and there are tremendous numbers of plants and animals that have adapted"},{"time":124000,"text":"to make their way and their life in the canopy."},{"time":126000,"text":"Common groups, like the sloth here, have clear adaptations"},{"time":130000,"text":"for forest canopies, hanging on with their very strong claws."},{"time":133000,"text":"But I'd like to describe to you a more subtle kind of diversity"},{"time":136000,"text":"and tell you about the ants."},{"time":138000,"text":"There are 10,000 species of ants that taxonomists --"},{"time":141000,"text":"people who describe and name animals -- have named."},{"time":144000,"text":"4,000 of those ants live exclusively in the forest canopy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"One of the reasons I tell you about ants"},{"time":151000,"text":"is because of my husband, who is in fact an ant taxonomist"},{"time":154000,"text":"and when we got married, he promised to name an ant after me, which he did --"},{"time":158000,"text":"Procryptocerus nalini, a canopy ant."},{"time":160000,"text":"We've had two children, August Andrew and Erika"},{"time":163000,"text":"and actually, he named ants after them."},{"time":165000,"text":"So we may be the only family that has an ant named after each one of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"But my passion -- in addition to Jack and my children --"},{"time":173000,"text":"are the plants, the so-called epiphytes,"},{"time":175000,"text":"those plants that grow up on trees."},{"time":178000,"text":"They don't have roots that go into trunks nor to the forest floor."},{"time":182000,"text":"But rather, it is their leaves that are adapted"},{"time":184000,"text":"to intercept the dissolved nutrients that come to them in the form of mist and fog."},{"time":189000,"text":"These plants occur in great diversity,"},{"time":192000,"text":"over 28,000 species around the world."},{"time":194000,"text":"They grow in tropical forests like this one"},{"time":197000,"text":"and they also grow in temperate rainforests, that we find in Washington state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"These epiphytes are mainly dominated by the mosses."},{"time":203000,"text":"One thing I want to point out is that underneath these live epiphytes,"},{"time":207000,"text":"as they die and decompose, they actually construct an arboreal soil,"},{"time":211000,"text":"both in the temperate zone and in the tropics."},{"time":214000,"text":"And these mosses, generated by decomposing,"},{"time":218000,"text":"are like peat moss in your garden."},{"time":220000,"text":"They have a tremendous capacity for holding on to nutrients and water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"One of the surprising things I discovered"},{"time":226000,"text":"is that, if you pull back with me on those mats of epiphytes,"},{"time":229000,"text":"what you'll find underneath them are connections, networks"},{"time":233000,"text":"of what we call canopy roots."},{"time":235000,"text":"These are not epiphyte roots:"},{"time":237000,"text":"these are roots that emerge from the trunk and branch of the host trees themselves."},{"time":240000,"text":"And so those epiphytes are actually paying the landlord a bit of rent"},{"time":244000,"text":"in exchange for being supported high above the forest floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"I was interested, and my canopy researcher colleagues have been interested"},{"time":251000,"text":"in the dynamics of the canopy plants that live in the forest."},{"time":254000,"text":"We've done stripping experiments"},{"time":256000,"text":"where we've removed mats of epiphytes"},{"time":258000,"text":"and looked at the rates of recolonization."},{"time":260000,"text":"We had predicted that they would grow back very quickly"},{"time":263000,"text":"and that they would come in encroaching from the side."},{"time":265000,"text":"What we found, however, was that they took an extremely long time --"},{"time":269000,"text":"over 20 years -- to regenerate,"},{"time":271000,"text":"starting from the bottom and growing up."},{"time":273000,"text":"And even now, after 25 years,"},{"time":275000,"text":"they're not up there, they have not recolonized completely."},{"time":278000,"text":"And I use this little image to say"},{"time":281000,"text":"this is what happens to mosses."},{"time":283000,"text":"If it's gone, it's gone,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and if you're really lucky you might get something growing back from the bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"So, recolonization is really very slow."},{"time":291000,"text":"These canopy communities are fragile."},{"time":294000,"text":"Well, when we look out, you and I, over that canopy"},{"time":297000,"text":"of the intact primary forest,"},{"time":299000,"text":"what we see is this enormous carpet of carbon."},{"time":303000,"text":"One of the challenges that canopy researchers are attacking today"},{"time":306000,"text":"is trying to understand the amount of carbon that is being sequestered."},{"time":310000,"text":"We know it's a lot,"},{"time":312000,"text":"but we do not yet know the answers to how much,"},{"time":314000,"text":"and by what processes, carbon is being taken out of the atmosphere,"},{"time":318000,"text":"held in its biomass, and moving on through the ecosystem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"So I hope I've showed you that canopy-dwellers"},{"time":325000,"text":"are not just insignificant bits of green up high in the canopy"},{"time":328000,"text":"that Tarzan and Jane were interested in,"},{"time":330000,"text":"but rather that they foster biodiversity"},{"time":333000,"text":"contribute to ecosystem nutrient cycles,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and they also help to keep our global climate stable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"Up in the canopy, if you were sitting next to me"},{"time":343000,"text":"and you turned around from those primary forest ecosystems,"},{"time":346000,"text":"you would also see scenes like this."},{"time":348000,"text":"Scenes of forest destruction, forest harvesting"},{"time":350000,"text":"and forest fragmentation,"},{"time":352000,"text":"thereby making that intact tapestry of the canopy"},{"time":355000,"text":"unable to function in the marvelous ways that it has"},{"time":358000,"text":"when it is not disturbed by humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"I've also looked out on urban places like this"},{"time":363000,"text":"and thought about people who are disassociated from trees in their lives."},{"time":366000,"text":"People who grew up in a place like this"},{"time":368000,"text":"did not have the opportunity to climb trees and form a relationship with trees"},{"time":372000,"text":"and forests, as I did when I was a young girl."},{"time":375000,"text":"This troubles me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"Here in 2009, you know, it's not an easy thing to be a forest ecologist,"},{"time":382000,"text":"gripping ourselves with these kinds of questions"},{"time":385000,"text":"and trying to figure out how we can answer them."},{"time":388000,"text":"And especially, you know, as a small brown woman"},{"time":391000,"text":"in a little college, in the upper northwest part of our country,"},{"time":394000,"text":"far away from the areas of power and money,"},{"time":397000,"text":"I really have to ask myself, \"What can I do about this?"},{"time":400000,"text":"How can I reconnect people with trees?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":403000,"text":"Well, I think that I can do something."},{"time":406000,"text":"I know that as a scientist, I have information"},{"time":409000,"text":"and as a human being, I can communicate with anybody,"},{"time":413000,"text":"inside or outside of academia."},{"time":415000,"text":"And so, that's what I've begin doing,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and so I'd like to unveil the International Canopy Network here."},{"time":421000,"text":"We consult to the media about canopy questions;"},{"time":424000,"text":"we have a canopy newsletter;"},{"time":426000,"text":"we have an email LISTSERV."},{"time":428000,"text":"And so we're trying to disseminate information about the importance of the canopy,"},{"time":431000,"text":"the beauty of the canopy,"},{"time":432000,"text":"the necessity of intact canopies,"},{"time":434000,"text":"to people outside of academia."},{"time":437000,"text":"We also recognize that a lot of the products that we make --"},{"time":441000,"text":"those videos and so forth --"},{"time":443000,"text":"you know, they don't reach everybody,"},{"time":446000,"text":"and so we've been fostering projects that reach people outside of academia,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and outside of the choir that most ecologists preach to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"Treetop Barbie is a great example of that."},{"time":456000,"text":"What we do, my students in my lab and I,"},{"time":458000,"text":"is we buy Barbies from Goodwill and Value Village,"},{"time":460000,"text":"we dress her in clothes that have been made by seamstresses"},{"time":464000,"text":"and we send her out with a canopy handbook."},{"time":467000,"text":"And my feeling is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"-- that we've taken this pop icon and we have just tweaked her a little bit"},{"time":476000,"text":"to become an ambassador who can carry the message"},{"time":479000,"text":"that being a woman scientist studying treetops is actually a really great thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483000,"text":"We've also made partnerships with artists,"},{"time":486000,"text":"with people who understand and can communicate the aesthetic beauty"},{"time":489000,"text":"of trees and forest canopies."},{"time":491000,"text":"And I'd like to just tell you one of our projects,"},{"time":493000,"text":"which is the generation of Canopy Confluences."},{"time":495000,"text":"What I do is I bring together scientists and artists of all kinds,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and we spend a week in the forest on these little platforms;"},{"time":501000,"text":"and we look at nature, we look at trees, we look at the canopy,"},{"time":504000,"text":"and we communicate, and exchange, and express what we see together."},{"time":509000,"text":"The results have been fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"I'll just give you a few examples."},{"time":513000,"text":"This is a fantastic installation by Bruce Chao"},{"time":515000,"text":"who is chair of the Sculpture and Glass Blowing Department"},{"time":518000,"text":"at Rhode Island School of Design."},{"time":520000,"text":"He saw nests in the canopy at one of our Canopy Confluences"},{"time":523000,"text":"in the Pacific Northwest, and created this beautiful sculpture."},{"time":527000,"text":"We've had dance people up in the canopy."},{"time":529000,"text":"Jodi Lomask, and her wonderful troupe Capacitor,"},{"time":533000,"text":"joined me in the canopy in my rainforest site in Costa Rica."},{"time":536000,"text":"They made a fabulous dance called \"Biome.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"They danced in the forest,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and we are taking this dance, my scientific outreach communications,"},{"time":547000,"text":"and also linking up with environmental groups,"},{"time":549000,"text":"to go to different cities and to perform"},{"time":551000,"text":"the science, the dance and the environmental outreach"},{"time":554000,"text":"that we hope will make a difference."},{"time":556000,"text":"We brought musicians to the canopy,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and they made their music -- and it's fantastic music."},{"time":561000,"text":"We had wooden flutists, we had oboists,"},{"time":563000,"text":"we had opera singers, we had guitar players,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and we had rap singers."},{"time":567000,"text":"And I brought a little segment to give you"},{"time":569000,"text":"of Duke Brady's \"Canopy Rap.\""},{"time":586000,"text":"(Music) That's Duke!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"This experience of working with Duke"},{"time":594000,"text":"also led me to initiate a program called Sound Science."},{"time":597000,"text":"I saw the power of Duke's song with urban youth --"},{"time":600000,"text":"an audience, you know, I as a middle-aged professor,"},{"time":602000,"text":"I don't have a hope of getting to --"},{"time":604000,"text":"in terms of convincing them of the importance of wildlands."},{"time":607000,"text":"So I engaged Caution, this rap singer,"},{"time":609000,"text":"with a group of young people from inner-city Tacoma."},{"time":612000,"text":"We went out to the forest, I would pick up a branch,"},{"time":614000,"text":"Caution would rap on it,"},{"time":616000,"text":"and suddenly that branch was really cool."},{"time":618000,"text":"And then the students would come into our sound studios,"},{"time":620000,"text":"they would make their own rap songs with their own beats."},{"time":623000,"text":"They ended up making a CD"},{"time":625000,"text":"which they took home to their family and friends,"},{"time":627000,"text":"thereby expressing their own experiences with nature"},{"time":630000,"text":"in their own medium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633000,"text":"The final project I'll talk about is one that's very close to my heart,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and it involves an economic and social value"},{"time":639000,"text":"that is associated with epiphytic plants."},{"time":642000,"text":"In the Pacific Northwest,"},{"time":644000,"text":"there's a whole industry of moss-harvesting"},{"time":647000,"text":"from old-growth forests."},{"time":649000,"text":"These mosses are taken from the forest;"},{"time":651000,"text":"they're used by the floriculture industry, by florists,"},{"time":654000,"text":"to make arrangements and make hanging baskets."},{"time":656000,"text":"It's a 265 million dollar industry"},{"time":659000,"text":"and it's increasing rapidly."},{"time":662000,"text":"If you remember that bald guy,"},{"time":664000,"text":"you'll know that what has been stripped off of these trunks"},{"time":666000,"text":"in the Pacific Northwest old-growth forest"},{"time":669000,"text":"is going to take decades and decades to come back."},{"time":672000,"text":"So this whole industry is unsustainable."},{"time":676000,"text":"What can I, as an ecologist, do about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"Well, my thought was that I could learn how to grow mosses,"},{"time":682000,"text":"and that way we wouldn't have to take them out of the wild."},{"time":685000,"text":"And I thought, if I had some partners that could help me with this,"},{"time":688000,"text":"that would be great."},{"time":690000,"text":"And so, I thought perhaps incarcerated men and women --"},{"time":692000,"text":"who don't have access to nature,"},{"time":694000,"text":"who often have a lot of time, they often have space,"},{"time":698000,"text":"and you don't need any sharp tools to work with mosses --"},{"time":700000,"text":"would be great partners."},{"time":702000,"text":"And they have become excellent partners."},{"time":704000,"text":"The best I can imagine."},{"time":707000,"text":"They were very enthusiastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"They were incredibly enthusiastic about the work."},{"time":717000,"text":"They learned how to distinguish different species of mosses,"},{"time":719000,"text":"which, to tell you the truth,"},{"time":721000,"text":"is a lot more than my undergraduate students at the Evergreen College can do."},{"time":724000,"text":"And they embraced the idea that they could help develop a research design"},{"time":729000,"text":"in order to grow these mosses."},{"time":731000,"text":"We've been successful as partners"},{"time":733000,"text":"in figuring out which species grow the fastest,"},{"time":735000,"text":"and I've just been overwhelmed with how successful this has been."},{"time":738000,"text":"Because the prison wardens were very enthusiastic about this as well,"},{"time":743000,"text":"I started a Science and Sustainability Seminar in the prisons."},{"time":747000,"text":"I brought my scientific colleagues and sustainability practitioners into the prison."},{"time":752000,"text":"We gave talks once a month,"},{"time":754000,"text":"and that actually ended up implementing"},{"time":756000,"text":"some amazing sustainability projects at the prisons --"},{"time":759000,"text":"organic gardens, worm culture, recycling,"},{"time":762000,"text":"water catchment and beekeeping. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"Our latest endeavor,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"with a grant"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"from the Department of Corrections at Washington state,"},{"time":772000,"text":"they've asked us to expand this program to three more prisons."},{"time":776000,"text":"And our new project is having the inmates and ourselves"},{"time":778000,"text":"learn how to raise the Oregon spotted frog"},{"time":781000,"text":"which is a highly endangered amphibian in Washington state and Oregon."},{"time":784000,"text":"So they will raise them -- in captivity, of course --"},{"time":787000,"text":"from eggs to tadpoles and onward to frogs."},{"time":791000,"text":"And they will have the pleasure, many of them,"},{"time":796000,"text":"of seeing those frogs that they've raised from eggs and helped develop,"},{"time":799000,"text":"helped nurture, move out into protected wildlands"},{"time":802000,"text":"to augment the number of endangered species out there in the wild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807000,"text":"And so, I think for many reasons --"},{"time":809000,"text":"ecological, social, economic and perhaps even spiritual --"},{"time":812000,"text":"this has been a tremendous project"},{"time":814000,"text":"and I'm really looking forward to"},{"time":816000,"text":"not only myself and my students doing it,"},{"time":819000,"text":"but also to promote and teach other scientists how to do this."},{"time":823000,"text":"As many of you are aware, the world of academia is a rather inward-looking one."},{"time":827000,"text":"I'm trying to help researchers move more outward"},{"time":831000,"text":"to have their own partnerships"},{"time":833000,"text":"with people outside of the academic community."},{"time":836000,"text":"And so I'm hoping that my husband Jack, the ant taxonomist,"},{"time":839000,"text":"can perhaps work with Mattel to make Taxonomist Ken."},{"time":842000,"text":"Perhaps Ben Zander and Bill Gates could get together"},{"time":848000,"text":"and make an opera about AIDS."},{"time":850000,"text":"Or perhaps Al Gore and Naturally 7 could make a song about climate change"},{"time":855000,"text":"that would really make you clap your hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"So, although it's a little bit of a fantasy, I think it's also a reality."},{"time":861000,"text":"Given the duress that we're feeling environmentally in these times,"},{"time":865000,"text":"it is time for scientists to reach outward,"},{"time":867000,"text":"and time for those outside of science to reach towards academia as well."},{"time":874000,"text":"I started my career with trying to understand the mysteries of forests"},{"time":879000,"text":"with the tools of science."},{"time":881000,"text":"By making these partnerships that I described to you,"},{"time":884000,"text":"I have really opened my mind and, I have to say, my heart"},{"time":888000,"text":"to have a greater understanding,"},{"time":890000,"text":"to make other discoveries about nature and myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"When I look into my heart, I see trees --"},{"time":897000,"text":"this is actually an image of a real heart --"},{"time":899000,"text":"there are trees in our hearts,"},{"time":901000,"text":"there are trees in your hearts."},{"time":903000,"text":"When we come to understand nature,"},{"time":905000,"text":"we are touching the most deep, the most important parts of our self."},{"time":910000,"text":"In these partnerships, I have also learned"},{"time":913000,"text":"that people tend to compartmentalize themselves"},{"time":916000,"text":"into IT people, and movie star people, and scientists,"},{"time":920000,"text":"but when we share nature,"},{"time":922000,"text":"when we share our perspectives about nature,"},{"time":925000,"text":"we find a common denominator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Finally, as a scientist and as a person"},{"time":932000,"text":"and now, as part of the TED community,"},{"time":936000,"text":"I feel that I have better tools"},{"time":939000,"text":"to go out to trees, to go out to forests, to go out to nature,"},{"time":943000,"text":"to make new discoveries about nature --"},{"time":946000,"text":"and about humans' place in nature"},{"time":948000,"text":"wherever we are and whomever you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":954000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}